               \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e        \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eQuick Links\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                                                                                    \u003cul\u003e\n                \u003cli\u003e\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                        \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#acer-launches-new-connect-m6e-5g-mobile-hotspot\"\u003eAcer Launches New Connect M6E 5G Mobile Hotspot\u003c/a\u003e\n                                        \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\n                                                                                            \u003cul\u003e\n                \u003cli\u003e\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                        \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#the-connect-m6e-5g-mobile-hotspot-is-just-what-i-need\"\u003eThe Connect M6E 5G Mobile Hotspot Is Just What I Need\u003c/a\u003e\n                                        \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\n            \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCES 2025 is a dazzling array of new tech, so I didn\u0026#39;t expect one of my favorite new devices to be a 5G hotspot. Acer\u0026#39;s new Connect M6E 5G mobile Wi-Fi hotspot is just that—a surprisingly great package that\u0026#39;s perfect for anyone who travels about.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"acer-launches-new-connect-m6e-5g-mobile-hotspot\"\u003e\n                        Acer Launches New Connect M6E 5G Mobile Hotspot\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAcer\u0026#39;s new Connect M6E 5G mobile hotspot ticks all the boxes: support for physical SIM and eSIM, 2x2 MIMO, NFC touch to connect, and, topping it off, Wi-Fi 6E connectivity. You can also connect up to 20 devices simultaneously, which makes it handy to keep in your bag or even take to the office, while the built-in screen makes it easy to navigate the various settings menus.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIt has an 8,000mAh battery that will keep the hotspot up and running for 28 hours, and it supports fast charging over USB-C. \u003cspan\u003eFurthermore, it\u0026#39;s built to \u0026#34;military-grade standards\u0026#34; (though there are \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/what-mil-std-810g-is-why-it-doesnt-mean-what-you-think/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eissues with companies using the MIL-STD-810G\u003c/a\u003e) and has an IP68 water and dust resistance rating.\u003c/span\u003e That means you can submerge the hotspot at up to 1.5 meters for up to 30 minutes—not bad for a portable 5G Wi-Fi router.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Gavin Phillips\\/MakeUseOf\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1400\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"acer connect m6e 5g wifi router close up of screen\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/acer-connect-m6e-5g-wifi-router-close-up-of-screen.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eGavin Phillips/MakeUseOf\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe other big feature on this new 5G hotspot is SignalScan. Basically, this tech enables the Connect M6E to jump between 5G networks for different providers and has support for more than 135 countries worldwide.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSo, if you\u0026#39;re heading to a new country, you could \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-airalo-esim-revolutionized-my-travels/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003egrab an eSIM from Airalo\u003c/a\u003e, load it onto your Connect M6E, and let it switch between 5G networks as required. It means you\u0026#39;ll never be far from a connection, keeping you online when you need it most.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"the-connect-m6e-5g-mobile-hotspot-is-just-what-i-need\"\u003e\n                        The Connect M6E 5G Mobile Hotspot Is Just What I Need\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt might be that I\u0026#39;m writing this at CES 2025, and Wi-Fi is notoriously irritating here, but I\u0026#39;m impressed with Acer\u0026#39;s new unit. What really stands out is the option to load an eSIM onto the Connect M6E and have it connect to a wide range of networks.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThat alone is a fantastic reason to pick up the Connect M6E—you\u0026#39;ll never be offline for long! The Acer Connect M6E 5G mobile hotspot will be available from Q2 2025 and starts at $249.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
